page.title: 13WILDLIFE 4
page.content: BIRD LIFE Bird life is very varied and includes several of the hawk family - buzzard, merlin, sparrow-hawk and kestrel. The buzzard, sometimes known as the small golden eagle, is fairly numerous. Until myxamatosis killed off many of the rabbits, it was these that made up a high proportion of a buzzard's diet. This bird is also the enemy of snakes. There are grouse, blackcock, woodcock snipe and what is also known to be on the moor and is surprising is that there are also wild duck and heron. OTHER ANIMALS The hare, badger, fox, weasel and stote are common.
